v0.1.16: Paperwik branding + Windows Terminal launcher + zero-touch UI

The big "make this feel like an app for a non-technical 77yo" pass.

Vault rename: ~/Knowledge -> ~/Paperwik
  Product name and folder name now match. ~25 files touched (skills,
  scripts, hooks, install.ps1, docs, templates). knowledge.db filename
  unchanged - it's the type of thing, not branding.

Template cleanup
  Removed Starter Project (placeholder cruft from early scaffolding).
  Added userIgnoreFilters to .obsidian/app.json so Obsidian hides
  CLAUDE.md, index.md, log.md, knowledge.db, eval.json, .scaffolded
  from the file explorer. End user sees only their actual content.

NEW step 7: Windows Terminal install
  WT becomes the polished launcher window for Paperwik. Win 11 22H2+
  has it preinstalled; older Windows installs via winget. Falls back
  to opening the Microsoft Store page if winget unavailable.

Step 8 extended (was just plugin+vault; now also handles UI):
  (a) git clone plugin (existing)
  (b) merge ~/.claude/settings.json (existing)
  (c) run scaffolder (existing)
  (d) NEW: convert assets/paperwik-icon.png to ICO via System.Drawing
      one-time per machine, cached at %LOCALAPPDATA%\Paperwik\
  (e) NEW: add "Paperwik" profile + Catppuccin-Mocha color scheme to
      Windows Terminal's settings.json. Profile auto-runs claude at
      ~/Paperwik on launch, soft dark theme, 13pt Cascadia Code,
      hidden scrollbar, generous padding.
  (f) NEW: create Paperwik.lnk in BOTH the Start menu and on the
      Desktop, both pointing at `wt.exe -p Paperwik` with the
      Paperwik icon. One-click launch.
  (g) NEW: register ~/Paperwik in %APPDATA%\obsidian\obsidian.json
      with open=true. Obsidian opens directly into the vault on
      first launch (no "create vault" dialog). Existing vaults
      get open=false so Obsidian doesn't try to open multiple at
      once.

Asset bundle
  Added assets/paperwik-icon.png (1000x1000 PNG with alpha) - the cyan
  crown-in-a-Q logo. Used as the icon in the WT profile (PNG works
  for WT) and converted to ICO for the .lnk shortcuts.

Final-message rewrite
  No more "open PowerShell, type cd ~, type claude". Now just:
  "Click the Paperwik icon on your Desktop or in your Start menu."
  Non-technical users never see PowerShell after install completes.

Step labels tightened: step 3 no longer says "Paperwik runs in
PowerShell" (misleading now that we have the WT launcher); step 8
title summarizes what it actually does.

Renumbered to 8 total steps. Banner says "Setting up in 8 steps.
Expect 8-10 minutes on typical home internet."
